column3:
Maru awaits you with an appraising look.

※Please note that the difficulty of this quest has been synced to your current level. Furthermore, you may not proceed with a class or job that is different from when you accepted this quest.
Obtain clumps of sticky moss at the Font of Maya.
Deliver the baskets of sticky moss to Maru.
I've been lookin' for you, <Split(<Highlight>ObjectParameter(1)</Highlight>, ,1)/>. I'm in need of a strong swimmer, and you look like you could keep up with a hippo in the water.
A friend of mine just came back from Yedlihmad, bearin' a request from Kancana herself...
The Font of Maya is in sore need of a deep cleanin', and we─which means <Emphasis>you</Emphasis>─gotta help. Kancana wants the moss gatherin' along the stone walls cleared away.

An' as you know, I don't like to see anythin' go to waste, so I'm thinkin' I might find a use for the moss. Take these baskets with you and bring back whatever you find growin' under the water's surface.
You're lookin' as dry as a hippo bakin' under the sun. Did you manage to gather the moss?
Ah, good─I was worried you'd take one look at them waters and think better of your choices. I'll let Kancana know that the temple should be lookin' a bit more pristine.
As luck would have it, hippos go mad for this moss. An' it don't hurt that it provides them with all the nutrients a growin' 'pot needs! Well, how about a bite?
Hahaha! I'm just kiddin'. I know you've got much more refined tastes─maybe you can indulge 'em with this bit of coin? I even know a service that offers fast, fresh grub, delivered right to you...
